remarks.p:
Also, remember that the GetLEDInstanceName and GetLEDInstance methods return a singleton instance of the LED object(s). Calling dispose for an LED object invalidates all references to that LED. For example:
LED appLed1 = LED.GetLEDInstance("Application");
...
LED appLed2 = LED.GetLEDInstance("Application"); // appLed2 == appLed1
...
appLed2.Dispose(); // releases all LED resources, appLed1 is now invalid too
...
appLed1.Dispose(); // !! Error !! Will throw an exception
// this is correct, a new LED object will be returned. appLed1 = LED.GetLEDInstance("Application");

