@deprecated This method has been replaced by Trigger namespace The Trigger property allows an application to determine which softkey is used to initiate a barcode scan.
The Trigger property can have one of the following values: * 0 = disabled * 1 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the II softkey. * 2 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the I softkey. * 3 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the UP softkey. * 4 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the DOWN softkey. * 5 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the LEFT softkey. * 6 = Barcode scans will be initiated by the RIGHT softkey.
The default value is 1 (the II key will initiate a barcode scan).
This property is only meaningful on a netpad.
The ApplySettingChanges method must be called in order to force the scanner configuration changes to take effect.

